Fix sys.path ordering for coverage under Bazel.

The current directory is first in sys.path, which causes test imports to
shadow modules of the same name.  Move it to the end before anything from
coverage is imported.

This is the same change as @rules_python//python/private:coverage.patch but
updated for coverage >=7.13 whose __main__.py added blank lines between
top-level statements.

diff --git a/coverage/__main__.py b/coverage/__main__.py
--- a/coverage/__main__.py
+++ b/coverage/__main__.py
@@ -6,7 +6,8 @@
 from __future__ import annotations
 
 import sys
+sys.path.append(sys.path.pop(0))
 
 from coverage.cmdline import main
 
 sys.exit(main())
